&lt;h1&gt;Sister/Charge Nurse - Day Surgery Unit&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6: £32,933 - £39,681 per annum, incl HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time/Fixed Term - 6 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, flexible and hard-working nurse to take on a senior role within the DSU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will assist in leading the nursing team in the provision of high quality; research based nursing care; leading shifts and taking responsibility for the efficient allocation of staff and resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post involves clinical, managerial and teaching duties so the successful candidate will be a Registered Nurse with at least 2 years surgical nursing experience who displays a genuine interest in day surgery. Previous management experience is not necessary although evidence of a teaching qualification is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to your professional development and offer excellent opportunities to enhance your clinical and managerial skills with both in-house and external training programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to take on a senior role and feel that you could contribute towards the efficient running of this busy unit, why not express an interest?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or an informal visit please contact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Claire Phillips, Senior Sister on extension 6970 or Helen Whitsed, Matron on extension 6940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
